name: THE AFTERMATH OF GAMBLING $100,000 (MAX BET ROLL)
description:

Please make sure you watch his video on his channel, before this one.  With that in mind, after the boys risked $100,000 yesterday... we are BACK at the Casino firing $40,000 MORE!  Can we win HUGE, or will we get absolutely SMOKED? Thank you all so much for liking, subscribing, and dropping your thoughts in the comments. Even if you‚Äôre roasting me‚ÄîI still love you. You‚Äôre all beautiful, and I truly appreciate every single one of you for riding along on this crazy journey.  Wish me luck, and I‚Äôll see you in the next one! Let‚Äôs go to war.

Brettski stood at the edge of the high-limit pit, heart pounding like a war drum. Behind him: Robby, Bluff, and their newest ally‚ÄîNick, a smooth-talking poker degenerate from New Jersey they‚Äôd met the night before. The sting of losing $100,000 still hung in the air like cigarette smoke. But today? Vengeance.

Each of them peeled off ten grand in cash, stacking it into a single pile.

‚ÄúForty grand,‚Äù Brettski muttered. ‚ÄúOne shot to flip this.‚Äù

Bluff raised an eyebrow. ‚ÄúWhere?‚Äù

‚ÄúDragon Baccarat,‚Äù said Nick, cracking his knuckles. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs got the highest variance. We either double up‚Ä¶ or go home in silence.‚Äù

The dealer gave a slow nod as they sat down. First hand: Player wins. They were up five grand instantly.

Second hand: Banker wins. Back to square one.

The next ten minutes were a blur‚Äîbets flying, adrenaline rising, Nick screaming ‚ÄúParlay!‚Äù after every win. They built it up to $68,000‚Äîalmost there.

Then Robby saw it.

‚Äú$1,000 side bet‚ÄîPlayer pair,‚Äù he whispered.

‚ÄúDon‚Äôt do it,‚Äù Brettski warned. ‚ÄúThat‚Äôs how the devil gets you.‚Äù

Robby did it anyway. The cards hit: Player‚Äî7 of hearts, 7 of diamonds.

The pit roared. The side bet paid out 11-to-1.

They hit $79,000.

‚ÄúTwenty-one grand away,‚Äù Bluff grinned. ‚ÄúLet‚Äôs finish this.‚Äù

But that‚Äôs when the pit boss stepped in.

‚ÄúGentlemen, upstairs guests would like a word,‚Äù he said, voice calm but cold. ‚ÄúThey've been watching your little comeback. They want to offer you a shortcut to six figures.‚Äù

‚ÄúWhat kind of shortcut?‚Äù Nick asked.

The pit boss gestured to the service elevator in the back, guarded by two men in suits.

‚ÄúHigh-stakes poker. No cameras. One hand. Double or nothing.‚Äù

Brettski glanced at the others.

‚ÄúDo we walk away winners‚Ä¶ or take the elevator?‚Äù

The doors opened with a chime.

No one moved.
